description: Holger Rune (DEN) meets Jack Draper (GBR) in the 2025 BNP Paribas Open final, the first ATP Masters 1000 title match between two players born in the 2000s. Rune defeated Daniil Medvedev in the semis with sharp tactics, while Draper edged past Carlos Alcaraz, displaying power and resilience. Rune leads their head-to-head 1-0, having won their 2024 Cincinnati clash in straight sets.

title: Jakub Mensik (CZE) vs Novak Djokovic (SRB) - Final - Miami Open 2025 - presented by Itaú - ATP 1000
description: 19-year-old Mensik, the Czech phenom, blasts into his first Masters final—taking down Top 10 giants with missile serves and fearless power. One win from history as youngest Miami champ ever.Across the net: Djokovic. The old lion prowls for his 7th Miami throne—still devouring dreamers.Tonight, fire meets fortress. The future charges at forever.

title: Lorenzo MUSETTI (ITA) vs Carlos ALCARAZ (ESP) - Final Rolex Monte Carlo Masters - ATP 1000 - Monaco
description: In the 2025 Monte Carlo Masters final, No. 2 seed Carlos Alcaraz meets Lorenzo Musetti in a high-stakes clay-court clash. Alcaraz, chasing his first Monte Carlo title, reached his seventh Masters 1000 final after defeating Davidovich Fokina. Musetti, now the third Italian to reach this final in the Open Era, earned his spot by edging past Alex de Minaur. Alcaraz leads their head-to-head 3–1, with Musetti’s lone win coming on clay in Hamburg (2022).

title: Casper Ruud (NOR) vs Jack Draper (GBR) - Final - Mutua Madrid Open 2025 - ATP 1000
description: In a first-ever ATP Tour meeting, clay-court specialist Casper Ruud takes on rising British star Jack Draper in the 2025 Madrid final. Ruud, a two-time Grand Slam finalist, is seeking his first Masters 1000 title. Draper, who claimed his breakthrough Masters win in Indian Wells earlier this season, aims to secure a second major trophy in 2025. A compelling battle awaits on the Caja Mágica clay.

title: Jannik Sinner (ITA) vs Carlos Alcaraz (ESP) - Cincinnati Open 2025 - ATP 1000
description: World No. 1 Jannik Sinner, holder of four Masters 1000 titles and 20 ATP singles trophies, comes into the Cincinnati final after winning two titles this season, including the Australian Open and Wimbledon. Across the net stands Carlos Alcaraz, with seven Masters crowns, 21 career titles, and five tournament victories already in 2025. Their rivalry remains one of the sport’s most exciting, with Alcaraz leading the head-to-head 8–5.

title: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA) - Final - Rolex Shanghai Masters ATP 1000
description: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA). First cousins meet in a historic Masters final after shock runs—qualifier Vacherot beat Djokovic; Rinderknech upset Medvedev to reach his first Masters title match. A family affair with big serves and fearless baseline hitting—expect tight sets and high drama in Shanghai.

title: Felix AUGER-ALIASSIME (CAN) vs Jannik SINNER (ITA) - Final - Rolex Paris Masters - Paris - 2025
description: The 2025 Rolex Paris Masters will be held from 27 October to 2 November at the new Paris La Defense Arena. Now in its 54th edition, this ATP Masters 1000 tournament features the world’s top players battling on indoor hard courts in both singles and doubles draws. With total prize money of €6,128,940, the event serves as the final major stop before the ATP Finals, promising a thrilling conclusion to the tennis season.

title: Jannik Sinner (ITA) vs Alexander Zverev (GER) -Mens Singles Final - Road Laver Arena - Australian O
description: The 2025 Australian Open men’s singles final sees defending champion and World No. 1 Jannik Sinner taking on World No. 2 Alexander Zverev. Sinner chases his third Grand Slam title after dominating Ben Shelton in the semifinals. Zverev, still in search of his first Grand Slam title, advanced after Novak Djokovic retired due to injury. A thrilling battle unfolds, with Sinner’s aggressive play clashing against Zverev’s powerful serves and groundstrokes.

title: Aryna Sabalenka vs Madison Keys (USA) - Womens Singles Final - Road Laver Arena - Australian Open
description: Aryna Sabalenka faces Madison Keys in the Australian Open women’s singles final. Sabalenka, the World No. 1, dominates their head-to-head 4-1 and looks unstoppable on Rod Laver Arena, riding a 20-match winning streak. Keys, ranked 19th, delivers a stunning run, defeating top seeds, including Iga Swiatek, with improved form under her husband-coach Bjorn Fratangelo. A clash of power and precision unfolds as they battle for the title.

title: S. Bolelli (ITA) / A. Vavassori (ITA) vs H. Heliovaara (FIN) / H. Patten (GBR) - Mens Doubles Fin
description: In the 2025 Australian Open men’s doubles final, the Italian duo Simone Bolelli and Andrea Vavassori faces Harri Heliovaara and Henry Patten. Bolelli and Vavassori showcase their exceptional teamwork, while Heliovaara and Patten bring momentum from a hard-fought semifinal victory over Kevin Krawietz and Tim Putz. The match delivers a thrilling contest between two in-form teams battling for the prestigious title.

title: K. Siniakova (CZE) / T. Townsend (USA) vs S. Hsieh (TPE) / J. Ostapenko (LAT) -Womens Doubles Fina
description: The 2025 Australian Open women’s doubles final features top seeds Kateřina Siniaková and Taylor Townsend against third seeds Hsieh Su-wei and Jeļena Ostapenko. Siniaková and Townsend, fresh off their Wimbledon triumph, aim for another Grand Slam title. Hsieh and Ostapenko, despite being a relatively new pairing, have impressed with their strong chemistry, including a hard-fought semifinal win over Gabriela Dabrowski and Erin Routliffe. A thrilling battle between two exceptional teams unfolds.

description: Defending champion Carlos Alcaraz faces World No. 1 Jannik Sinner in a highly anticipated final. Alcaraz aims to retain his title, while Sinner seeks his first Roland-Garros crown. Both players have showcased exceptional form throughout the tournament, setting the stage for a thrilling championship match.

title: Aryna SABALENKA vs Coco GAUFF (USA) - Womens Singles - Finals - Philippe-Chatrier Court - Roland G
description: World No. 1 Aryna Sabalenka takes on World No. 2 Coco Gauff in a blockbuster Roland-Garros final. With their head-to-head tied at 5–5, and both players chasing their first Roland-Garros crown, this rivalry reaches a new peak on the Paris clay. A Grand Slam classic in the making.

title: Marcel GRANOLLERS (ESP) / Horacio ZEBALLOS (ARG) vs Joe SALISBURY (GBR)/Neal SKUPSKI (GBR) - Mens
description: Fifth seeds Marcel Granollers and Horacio Zeballos face eighth seeds Joe Salisbury and Neal Skupski in a high-stakes final. Granollers and Zeballos, seeking their first Grand Slam title together after three previous final appearances, take on the British duo, who aim to become the first all-British team to win the Roland-Garros mens doubles since 1936. A compelling clash of experience and ambition on the Paris clay.

title: Anna DANILINA (KAZ) Aleksandra KRUNIC (SRB) vs Sara ERRANI (ITA) Jasmine PAOLINI (ITA) - Womens Dou
description: Second seeds Sara Errani and Jasmine Paolini take on Anna Danilina and Aleksandra Krunić in the womens doubles final. Errani and Paolini, finalists for the second consecutive year, aim to secure their first Roland-Garros title as a team against the unseeded duo of Danilina and Krunić

title: Jannik Sinner (ITA) vs Carlos Alcaraz (ESP) - Gentlemen’s Singles Final - Centre Court - Wimbledon 2
description: Top seed Jannik Sinner takes on defending champion Carlos Alcaraz in a blockbuster Wimbledon final. This is their fifth career meeting, with Alcaraz leading the head-to-head 3–1. Sinner is chasing his first Wimbledon crown, while Alcaraz aims for a historic third straight title. A generational battle on Centre Court.

title: Amanda Anisimova (USA) vs Iga Swiatek (POL) - Ladies’ Singles Final - Centre Court - Wimbledon 2025
description: A first-time Wimbledon champion will be crowned as Iga Świątek faces Amanda Anisimova. Świątek, a five-time Grand Slam winner, reaches her first final at SW19. Anisimova, playing her maiden major final, stunned world No. 1 Sabalenka in the semis. This is their first-ever meeting. Experience vs momentum — who will triumph on Centre Court?

title: Rinky Hijikata (AUS)/David Pel (NED) vs Julian Cash (GBR)/Lloyd Glasspool (GBR) - Gentlemens Doubl
description: British duo Lloyd Glasspool and Julian Cash contest their first Grand Slam final against Australia’s Rinky Hijikata and David Pel. The unseeded pair stunned the top seeds in the semi-finals. This is the first-ever meeting between the teams, with Glasspool and Cash bidding to become the first all-British Wimbledon men’s doubles champions since 1936.

title: Su-Wei Hsieh (TPE)/Jelena Ostapenko (LAT) vs Veronika Kudermetova/Elise Mertens (BEL) - Ladies’ Doub
description: Centre Court hosts the most anticipated showdowns of Wimbledon 2025, from title favourites to defending champions and unforgettable rivalries. Built in 1922 and equipped with a retractable roof since 2009, the venue ensures uninterrupted action and iconic atmosphere for over 15,000 fans. As the tournament’s most prestigious stage, Centre Court continues to deliver the drama, precision, and elegance that define The Championships.

title: Finals - Arab Elite Tennis Championship - 2025
description: 5th Arab Tennis Elite Tournament – Manama, Bahrain concludes with the Singles Final as Mohammad Al Qutb (Jordan) meets Aziz Al Waqaa (Tunisia) on the hard courts of the Public Security Officers Club. A 24-player elite field from the Arab Tennis Federation circuit features ATP and ITF-ranked competitors, alongside a parallel U16 Arab Juniors event. title: One Friday Fight 2025 - 137
description: ONE Friday Fights 137ONE closes 2025 with a stacked card at Lumpinee Stadium on December 19. Featherweight Muay Thai World Champion Tawanchai returns to kickboxing against the dangerous “Spirit Dragon” Liu Mengyang. The card also features Sam-A vs Jaosuayai, Yod-IQ vs Elbrus Osmanov, Suablack vs Pakorn, Jo Nattawut vs Mohammad Siasarani, Zhang Peimian vs Thongpoon, and more action-packed bouts.

title: Nants vs Paris - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
description: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s 14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germains 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Team – Round 1 - Longines Global Champions Tour - Rome, ITA
description: The GCL Team Round 1 opens the Rome leg at the Foro Italico. Two riders per squad chase fast, fault-free trips to set the overnight order and carry scores into Round 2. Expect tight time allowed, flowing lines, and smart tactics on stride counts and anchor placement as title contenders push for pole.

title: Team - Round 2 - Longines Global Champions Tour - Rome, ITA
description: The decisive GCL Team Round 2. Reverse-order start from Round 1, with every rail and second counting toward the combined team total. Strategic rider swaps and cool heads over a technical track shape the podium and precious championship points in a high-stakes Roman finish.

title: CSI5 - Longines Global Champions Tour - Rome, ITA
description: Top combinations tackle elite CSI5* classes at the Foro Italico. A technical track, tight time allowed and related lines test precision and power, with the fastest clears advancing to a jump-off. Expect fine margins, inside turns and bold strides as riders chase ranking points and momentum for the Grand Prix.

title: Grand Prix of Rome - Longines Global Champions Tour - Rome, ITA
description: The 1.60m LGCT Grand Prix: one round plus jump-off for big championship points and a golden ticket to the Prague Playoffs Super Grand Prix. Huge oxers, delicate verticals and a demanding time allowed reward brave riding and perfect stride control in a high-stakes Roman finale.

title: T100 Triathlon - PTO - World Tour 2025 Final - Doha
description: The T100 Triathlon World Tour Final lands in Doha/Lusail (10–13 December 2025) as the season-ending showdown that crowns the T100 World Champion. title: Egypt vs Zimbabwe - African Cup of Nations - Morocco 2025
description: This will be the third AFCON encounter between Egypt and Zimbabwe, with each of them taking place in North Africa. The two previous meetings produced Egyptian victories, both in the group stages: 2004 and 2019. This is Egypt’s 27th appearance at the CAF Africa Cup of Nations, a record in the history of the tournament. They have won it seven times – more than any other side – and have also reached the final in five of their last seven participations.

title: Tunisia vs Uganda - African Cup of Nations - Morocco 2025
description: This will be the third encounter between Tunisia and Uganda at AFCON, but also their first meeting in the tournament for 47 years. Tunisia won both of their previous matches, scoring six goals and conceding only one. This is Tunisia’s 22nd participation in the CAF Africa Cup of Nations, and their 17th in a row, the latter being a record in the history of the tournament. Their only AFCON title dates back to 2004, as hosts; since then, they’ve progressed past the quarter-finals only once, in 2019, losing in the third-place match.

title: Algeria vs Sudan - African Cup of Nations - Morocco 2025
description: This will be the first ever AFCON encounter between Algeria and Sudan. Sudan are unbeaten in their last two games against Algeria in all competitions, winning on penalties in the quarter finals of the African Nations Championship in August and a 0-0 draw in the FIFA Arab Cup earlier this month. Algeria are making their 21st appearance at the CAF Africa Cup of Nations. They will be attempting to win the trophy for the third time, after 1990 and 2019 – both previous victories were won on North African soil: at home in 1990 and in Egypt in 2019.
